Project Details :

1. Project Title 
Digital  Based Shape Pattern Generator using Python 

2. Problem Statement 
To design and develop a Python program that generates different geometric shape patterns 
such as square, rectangle, triangle, pyramid, and circle based on user input and digit-based size. 

3. Objective 
The objective of this project is to create a pattern generator program that accepts the shape 
name and size from the user and displays the corresponding pattern using loops and 
conditional statements in Python. 

4. Tools Used 
Python IDLE / Python Compiler 

5. Description 
•  This project generates different geometric shape patterns. 
•  The user enters the shape name. 
•  The user enters the size (digit). 
•  The program prints the selected shape pattern using loops. 
•  Circle pattern is generated using the mathematical formula (x² + y² ≤ r²). 

6. Algorithm 
Start 
1. Read the shape name from the user. 
2. Read the size (digit) from the user. 
3. If shape is square → print n × n star pattern. 
4. If shape is rectangle → print n rows and (n+3) columns. 
5. If shape is triangle → print increasing star pattern. 
6. If shape is pyramid → print centered increasing pattern. 
7. If shape is circle → use formula (x² + y² ≤ r²) to print circle pattern. 
8. Else display invalid message. 
9. Stop 

7. Program (Python Code) 

